Why Functions?

  - capture pattern
  - good to break it up

  `return;` can quit out of function or loop

  interrupt program => ctrl - c


  Arrays¡¡¡

    - collection of things
    - * all same type *
    - fixed size

    Declaring:

    - `int[] a;`   ==> a = *new* int[4]
    - a is a reference to the array object
    - can refer to index i.e. a[0]
      - a.length -> compute the length

    - int[] b = {4, 5, 7, 422, 45544}   (shorthand)

    loop through:

    for(int i = 0; i < a.length; i++)
